occurrenceRemarks: Almost daily visitor. I almost literally stumbled into this bird this afternoon. Just above my head height. Chowing down on a female Cardinal. She had no problem with me watching as I stood just feet away from her perched in a Mulberry Tree. Last photo shows distended crop after meal. Temperature near 32 degrees Fahrenheit. We rose above freezing for a couple of hours today, above forecast of 29F.
